verse.lines:
{lang-eng}My soul, ask what thou wilt;
thou canst not be too bold;
since his own blood for thee he spilt,
what else can he withhold?{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Beyond thy utmost wants
his love and pow'r can bless;
to praying souls he always grants
more than they can express.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Since ’tis the Lord’s command,
My mouth we'll open wide;
Lord open Thou Thy bounteous hand,
That we may be supplied.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Thine image, Lord, bestow,
thy presence and thy love;
We ask to serve thee here below,
and reign with thee above.{/lang-eng}
